- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper specifically focuses on privacy in social media. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper may discuss software tools and techniques for anonymization and de-anonymization. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possibility as the paper discusses privacy concerns and risks for online users. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a less likely category, but may be relevant as the paper discusses anonymization techniques for user-generated data.
